Just hours later, shortly after 1pm, armed officers descended on the suburb and used tasers to overpower their suspect.

Salvador was charged with murdering Mrs Silva and assaulting a police office.

He appeared yesterday at Highbury Corner Magistrates' Corner in north London, where he was remanded in custody.

His next court appearance will be at the Old Bailey on Tuesday.

The 25-year-old was unemployed and was staying with a friend a few doors from the 82-year-old widow in Edmonton before her murder, according to information obtained by the Daily Mail.

