The would-be cage fighter left home 11 years ago. One friend said: ‘Nicholas is an only child and his parents brought him here from Nigeria. But when he was about 13 or 14 he left home.

'The truth is, he has never felt loved.'

A former classmate at Salisbury School, Edmonton, added: ‘We used to call him St Nicholas because he never got up to anything. He was always saying he wanted a girlfriend.’

Palmira Silva moved to London from her native Italy with her husband Domenico in the 1950s to start a new life.

They married, started a family and began a successful restaurant business with a string of cafes and snack bars across the city. 

